# Elasticsearch Integration

## Client Usage
- Use official Go Elasticsearch client (`go-elasticsearch/v8`)
- Implement proper connection pooling
- Handle connection failures gracefully
- Use context for request timeouts

## Index Management
- Create indices with proper mappings
- Use index aliases for zero-downtime updates
- Implement index lifecycle management
- Handle index versioning properly

## Document Operations
- Use bulk operations for multiple documents
- Implement proper error handling for failed operations
- Use appropriate refresh settings
- Handle document conflicts gracefully

## Search Implementation
- Use query DSL for complex searches
- Implement proper pagination
- Use aggregations for analytics
- Optimize search performance

## Data Modeling
- Design mappings for efficient searching
- Use appropriate field types
- Implement proper analyzers
- Consider search requirements when modeling

## Monitoring & Maintenance
- Monitor cluster health and performance
- Implement proper logging for operations
- Handle index maintenance tasks
- Monitor storage usage and growth
